title: Activists could be jailed for six months for protesting outside MPs’ homes
summary: A new law in England and Wales is set to criminalize protests outside the homes of Members of Parliament (MPs) as part of measures to address rising harassment complaints. This legislation aims to enhance the protection of lawmakers from disruptive demonstrations. The move reflects growing concerns over the safety and wellbeing of MPs amid increased public discourse and protests.
